<p>The <b>saker falcon</b> (<i>Falco cherrug</i>) is a very large <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Falcon" title="Falcon">falcon</a>. This species breeds from eastern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a> eastwards across <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asia" title="Asia">Asia</a> to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchuria" title="Manchuria">Manchuria</a>. It is mainly <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird_migration" title="Bird migration">migratory</a> except in the southernmost parts of its range, wintering in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopia" title="Ethiopia">Ethiopia</a>, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arabian_peninsula" title="Arabian peninsula" class="mw-redirect">Arabian peninsula</a>, northern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan" title="Pakistan">Pakistan</a> and western <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China" title="China">China</a>.</p>
<p></p>
